edu.iastate.ansci.flip.database

Class PopulationDatabase

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.iastate.ansci.flip.database.PopulationDatabase

  • public class PopulationDatabase
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provide methods to save, update and remove populations stored at the temporal and persistent databases. The identifier of a population in a temporal database is the username of an online instructor who is currently accessing it. An instructor may have many populations stored at the persistent database, which are identified by a unique integer identifier which is greater than zero. If a population has a NULL_ID identifier, it means that it has not been stored into the permanent database and only exists in the temporal database. An online instructor has only one population stored at the temporal database. This population is called as the instructor's active population. Therefore if this active population is not saved at the persistent database, this data will be lost when the instructor loads another population.
    Author:
    patricio
